The IFE-based sensors were constructed for the detection of L-Cys and there was clearly variation for the PL intensity of QNs. From Fig. 6
                        , it could be seen that there was gradually enhancement of the PL intensity of QNs system with the increase of L-Cys concentrations from 20 μM to 400 μM, the possible reason was that L-Cys was easily deprotonated in aqueous solution, and the deprotonated L-Cys could react with Ag NPs to formed covalent bonds of S-Ag due to the existence of thiol group. Therefore, the QNs system can be designed to detect L-Cys based on the competition mechanism between L-Cys, Ag NPs, and CdTeS QDs. Compared with CdTeS QDs, L-Cys was easier to combine with Ag NPs because the solubility product of CdS and Ag2S are 8.0 × 10−27 and 6.3 × 10−50, respectively. This destroyed the combination of CdTeS QDs and Ag NPs when the introduction of L-Cys, resulting the recovery of PL intensity (Scheme 1
                        ).
